      • getImageDownloadSuccessful

        boolean getImageDownloadSuccessful()
        Returns the status of the image download on this in-app message. If the image specified by getRemoteImageUrl() could not be downloaded successfully then this should return false. Returns false by default.
        Returns:
        true if the image was downloaded successfully

      • setLocalImageUrl

        void setLocalImageUrl(java.lang.String imageUrl)
        Sets the image on this in-app message to a local uri. If a bitmap and local image url are both set, the bitmap will be prioritized. Local uris will be prioritized over remote uris. To set a remote uri, use setRemoteImageUrl(String) See setBitmap(android.graphics.Bitmap)
        Parameters:
        imageUrl - Url for the desired image.

      • setImageDownloadSuccessful

        void setImageDownloadSuccessful(boolean imageDownloadSuccessful)
        Sets the status of the image download on this in-app message. See getImageDownloadSuccessful(). See IInAppMessage#getImageDownloadSuccessful().
        Parameters:
        imageDownloadSuccessful - value for the success of the image download

      • setRemoteImageUrl

        void setRemoteImageUrl(java.lang.String imageUrl)
        Sets the image on this in-app message to a remote uri. If a bitmap and remote image url are both set, the bitmap will be prioritized. Local uris will be prioritized over remote uris. To set a local uri, use setLocalImageUrl(String) See setBitmap(android.graphics.Bitmap)
        Parameters:
        imageUrl - Url for the desired image.

      • setBitmap

        void setBitmap(android.graphics.Bitmap bitmap)
        Explicitly sets the bitmap on this in-app message. If a bitmap and image url are both set, the bitmap will be prioritized. See setLocalImageUrl(String) See setRemoteImageUrl(String)
        Parameters:
        bitmap - An optimized bitmap image.
